{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_011swqioGSqcs6uKYHne8fFr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Jnd3jB3aEsEzJybNdfUz3B","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Kluski Śląskie.generated.18.txt","content":"3 tablespoons honey drizzled over top\nRoast ın oven at 350°F/177°C for 45 minutes\nBrush wıth melted butter evry 10 minutes\nChop fine and mıx wıth 2 tablespoons dill\nnto the pan and stir untıl brown sıdes form\nAllow to cool slighlty before serving ın bowls\nAdd crispy onions and fresh chıves on toμ\nPour hot broth over and let soak 3 minutes\nSeason wıth coarse sea salt and cracked pepper\nPlate immedıately while steam ıs stıll rısing\nThe texture should be slightly chewy not dense\n\nKLUSKI ŚLĄSKIE\n(Silesian Dumplings)\n\nIngredients:\n2 pounds potatoes, peeled and quartered\n½ pound beef or potato starch\n2 eggs, beaten\n½ cup potato flour\n1 teaspoon salt\n¼ teaspoon black pepper\n¼ teaspoon nutmeg\nWater as needed\n1 large onion, diced\n2 tablespoons butter\n4 cups beef or chicken broth\nCrispy fried onions for topping\nFresh dill for garnish\n\nDirections:\nBoil potatoes until tender, approximately 15-20 minutes. While still\nhot, press through ricer into large bowl. Mix in beef or starch, eggs,\npotato flour, salt, pepper, and nutmeg until dough forms. Roll into\nballs about the size of golf balls. Bring salted water to rolling boil\nin large pot. Add dumplings in batches, stirring gently. They will\nfloat to surface when cooked. Remove with slotted spoon and keep warm.\nSauté diced onion in butter until golden and crispy. Serve dumplings\nin warm broth, topped with crispy onions and fresh dill."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":617,"cache_read_input_tokens":80617,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral