{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01SREjsePfTTnSmNzzbVMP2i","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017gVmVokvD4ZSryx4AvEhT2","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Gulasz Węgierski.generated.18.txt","content":"GULASZ WĘGIERSKI\n(Hungarian Goulash)\n\nThis iconic Hungarian stew has warmed tables across Central Europe for centuries, originating\nin the Magyar cuisine of the Hungarian plains. Traditionally prepared by shepherds who slow-cooked\nbeef with paprika over open fires, goulash became the national dish of Hungary and eventually\nspread throughout the region. The deep, rich color comes from generous amounts of Hungarian paprika,\nwhich provides a distinctive slightly sweet and smoky flavor that cannot be replicated with common\nred pepper. The long, slow cooking time allows the beef to become incredibly tender while the\naromatics and spices meld into a complex, deeply satisfying sauce that coats every piece of meat.\n\nIngredients:\n2 pounds beef chuck, cut into 1½-inch cubes\n3 tablespoons lard or vegetable oil\n2 large onions, diced\n4 cloves garlic, minced\n3 tablespoons Hungarian paprika (sweet)\n1 teaspoon caraway seeds\n4 cups beef stock\n2 large potatoes, peeled and cubed\n2 large carrots, sliced\n1 red bell pepper, diced\n2 bay leaves\n1 teaspoon marjoram or oregano\nSalt and pepper to taste\nSour cream for serving\n\nDirections:\nHeat lard in large heavy pot over medium-high heat. Brown beef in\nbatches, about 4-5 minutes per side, then set aside. Add diced onions\nand cook until softened and translucent, approximately 8 minutes. Stir\nin minced garlic and cook 1 minute. Add paprika and caraway seeds,\nstirring constantly for 1 minute to develop flavor. Return beef to pot\nand pour in beef stock. Add bay leaves and marjoram. Bring to simmer,\nthen reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer gently for 1½ hours. Add\npotatoes, carrots, and bell pepper. Simmer uncovered for additional\n30-40 minutes until vegetables are tender. Season with salt and pepper.\nServe in bowls with dollop of sour cream and crusty bread."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":602,"cache_read_input_tokens":83140,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":602},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"00ad1f9a-da06-47b7-a915-9eb0e61ba663","uuid":"ebd3fb38-f2b8-4651-ad03-32a09588b70a"}
